Consider the piecewise function 

\[ h(x) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
ax^3 + bx^2 + cx + d, & \text{if } x > 4, \\
x^3 - 3x^2 + ex + f, & \text{if } 0 < x \le 4, \\
4x^3 + gx + h, & \text{if } x \le 0.
\end{array}
\right. \] 

Determine the values of \( a, b, c, d, e, f, g, \) and \( h \) such that the function \( h(x) \) is continuous everywhere. Then, compute the value of \( a^2 + b^2 + c^2 + d^2 + e^2 + f^2 + g^2 + h^2 \).
